{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:15:58.930478+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 85bcd17c1bfa3c3b6179c895760d3aa82499a35f)", "id": "lc_240c6234-5c2d-4a20-9154-d032e39e37e6"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/bin/bash\n# Yes, I know this is bad. It uses a custom chunk-based file fingerprinter,\n# but it's not ready just yet and has shortcomings that have to be patched\n# by this bash script. I'm working on it.\nrm -rf build\nwebdev build\ncd build/images && mv * ../ && cd ../\n\ndart ../../../fingerprint/bin/fingerprint.dart\n\nfor i in $(find . -type f | egrep '\\.(svg|png|jpeg|jpg)$'); do\n    mv \"$i\" ./images/$i\ndone\n\ncd ../\n# firebase deploy", "id": "lc_5dba83af-93ff-4b61-9805-5ae50c4b0433"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4c1b9b25-a423-4de4-8d89-2024395804b2", "tool_call_id": "call_01_3s06IYwg6tYeqMqTPZxW4964", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:12.816735+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the README and repository structure, here is the ordered sequence:\n\n---\n\n### 0. Prerequisite (from the README)\nThe TMDB configuration file must be renamed before the project will compile:\n```bash\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n```\n\n### (a) Install Flutter web tooling\nEnable the Flutter web platform (requires Flutter SDK already installed):\n```bash\nflutter config --enable-web\n```\n\nThen add the web platform to the existing Flutter project inside the `mobile/` directory (the project predates Flutter web and has no `web/` folder):\n```bash\ncd mobile && flutter create --platforms=web .\n```\n\n### (b) Fetch dependencies\nPull all Dart/Flutter packages for the mobile project (which also references the local `core` package):\n```bash\ncd mobile && flutter pub get\n```\n\n### (c) Produce a release web build under `build/web/`\nBuild the Flutter app for the web target in release mode:\n```bash\ncd mobile && flutter build web\n```\n\nThis places the release output under **`mobile/build/web/`**.\n\n---\n\n**Important note:** The README describes the original web offering as an **AngularDart** app (the `web/` directory at the repo root), built with `webdev build` (output goes to `web/build/`). The instructions above instead build the **Flutter** mobile app (`mobile/`) for the web, which is what your request for “Flutter web tooling” and a `build/web/` output implies.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1185, "prompt_tokens": 13959, "total_tokens": 15144, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 845, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 13440}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 13440, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 519}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "66084f6b-890c-4659-a4c6-afe0c324ddde", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3ba-57d3-7060-9c87-c89a8022fd95-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13959, "output_tokens": 1185, "total_tokens": 15144, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 13440}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 845}}}}]}}}
